The song has character, it does what pop music does and it's okay. But it's not special, the message has no value in actual personal development, but if people think it helps it may help them for a while. She just tells girls exactly what they need to hear, even if it'll never be fulfilling. It's not my problem anyway, it's a fun song, good tune, good vibe and rhythm, lyrics are intrinsic bullshit but very creative and full of character. Gives a dreamy summer feeling. I hate the music video not just for all the beauty standards in men and women, there is just so much more. But I don't want to take your joy. Enjoy the song if you like it. Just saying that not every music enjoyer feels the same way and thinks this is perfect. But it certainly is art and for art you have to look very long to find IT. And it's very subjective what mirrors your soul and let's your mind in. If you found yourself here I am happy for you, for me this is just the mainstream. I don't want to be special, I am just different and very deep in my mind, trying to understand and feel everything, which get's me off the stream. Where I find the cold truth, some fragments of it hidden from society or beliefs and I can add this to my perfect working image of the world and life. Perfectly fulfilled in a world where everybody isn't and I can't help no one, because they won't listen and have to find a way that works for them themselves. I could have a philosophic crash out right now, but my thoughts are already taking more space than the absolute attention and understanding I could get or deserve.
